devdoc.details: A transformer that fills an ERC20 market sell/buy quote.      This transformer shortcuts bridge orders and fills them directly

ProtocolFeeUnfunded(uint256,uint256).details: Emitted when a trade is skipped due to a lack of funds      to pay the 0x Protocol fee.

params.ethNeeded: The current eth balance required to pay        the protocol fee.

die(address).details: Destruct this contract. Only callable by the deployer and will not      succeed in the context of a delegatecall (from another contract).

params.ethRecipient: The recipient of ETH held in this contract.

transform((bytes32,address,address,bytes.details: Sell this contract's entire balance of of `sellToken` in exchange      for `buyToken` by filling `orders`. Protocol fees should be attached      to this call. `buyToken` and excess ETH will be transferred back to the caller.

REFUND_RECEIVER_SENDER.details: If `refundReceiver` is set to this address, unpsent      protocol fees will be sent to the sender.

REFUND_RECEIVER_TAKER.details: If `refundReceiver` is set to this address, unpsent      protocol fees will be sent to the taker.
